      <section id="id2742097">
        <title>Assessment</title>
        <para id="id8943935"><emphasis effect="bold">LEARNING OUTCOME 4: </emphasis><emphasis effect="bold">WRITING</emphasis>The learner is able to write different kinds of factual and imaginative texts for a wide range of purposes.</para>
        <para id="id7476933">Assessment Standard</para>
        <para id="id3210280">We know this when the learner:</para>
        <para id="id4792205">4.4 applies knowledge of language at various levels:</para>
        <para id="id8458544">4.4.3 paragraph level:</para>
        <para id="id7205429">uses topic and supporting sentences to develop a coherent paragraph,</para>
        <para id="id8838826">uses appropriate grammar, spelling and punctuation.</para>
        <para id="id2911439"><emphasis effect="bold">LEARNING OUTCOME 6: </emphasis><emphasis effect="bold">LANGUAGE STRUCTURE AND USE</emphasis>The learner will know and be able to use the sounds, words and grammar of the language and interpret texts.</para>
        <para id="id3641160">Assessment Standard</para>
        <para id="id1170991747742">We know this when the learner:</para>
        <para id="id1170988524752">6.2 works with sentences:</para>
        <list id="id3789792" list-type="bulleted">
          <item>uses complex tenses correctly (e.g. past progressive – ‘She was watching TV when …’).</item>
        </list>
        <para id="id1170988213957"/>
      </section>
